Business Brief -- Lincoln Financial Corp.:
   Bank Holding Concern Posts
   Loss for the Fourth Quarter
Lincoln Financial's shares climbed $2 and were quoted at
$24.25 in late national over-the-counter trading Friday.
   In the fourth quarter of 1990, the bank holding company
earned $6.5 million, or 93 cents a share.
   The latest quarter includes provisions for loan losses of
$32.1 million, compared with $1.2 million in the same period
in 1990. As of Dec. 31, Lincoln said it had loan-loss
reserves of $60 million, compared with $18.2 million in 1990.
   The company said the loan-loss reserves and write-offs
were primarily centered on commercial loans to businesses and
commercial real-estate projects in the company's Lincoln
National Bank unit's market area.
   Lincoln Financial said it has authorized the immediate
search for a new president and chief executive officer.